spanGrp.span: ‘We get to Buenos Aires, right into town uh…
Se dajũ damĩũ BuenosAires Buenos Aires sĩska esteee
at the park’s corner there is a chuch, a Catholic one.
parke gicha ska iglesia kalu iglesia katolika
we come… when we leave, we turn… left;
se datse se (_) desãũ-ka-ra se të í guge-ra-wã jula jula shulë wa
we go straight to the left
jula shulë wa ñawösiga se bötöũ
and we get to an intersection.
there we turn to the right.
jesak ra se të í guge-ra-wã-nẽ jula mõĩ'
That way we get to the Olan crossing…
Jeska se të í guge-ra-wã-nẽ jula mõĩ' wa
Turning left we get to the Ceibo River side. At the Ceibo River is the bridge.
jula shulë wa se dateũ dagaũ Bikës kömĩ Bikës (r) Bikës ska puente blali
After the Ceibo River you go straight ahead, at your left there is Santa Maria.
Je Bikës ska ba dateũ ñawösiga ta jula shulë wa ra je rö Santa_Maria
Then you go straight; we go straight;
Je ñawösiga ba beteũ-nẽ sa dateũ sa dateũ ñawösiga
it goes, we go straight up to Ujarraz School.
Jera je desãũ ñawösiga sa dateũ je desãũ Eskuela Ujarras
At Ujarraz Scholl we are already in Ujarraz.
Eskuela Ujarras-ka ra ya se demĩũ kã' Ujarras
se mẽnẽũ ñawösiga je damĩũ San_Bisente
Je jula mõĩ wa je rö Guanakaste
To the right you get to El Carmen
Jula mõĩ wa e rö El_Carmen
and straight ahead is Santa Rosa.
